# Manual Testing Project – Letter Drafting Web Application

## Project Overview

This project contains **manual testing documentation** for the Letter Drafting Web Application.

The objective of this project was to perform **functional testing, UI testing, and navigation validation** on the web application and document the results using structured **test scenarios and test cases**.

Application Under Test (AUT):
https://letter-drafting.vercel.app

---

## Testing Scope

The following modules were tested:

• Landing Page
• Navigation Buttons
• Login Page
• Registration Page
• Payment Upload (QR Based Payment)
• URL Routing & Anchor Navigation
• UI Behavior and Validation Messages

---

## Testing Approach

The application was tested using **manual testing techniques**.
Test scenarios and test cases were written in **Excel format** with the following structure:

Test Case Fields:

• Test Case ID
• Scenario ID
• Module
• Title
• Preconditions
• Steps
• Test Data
• Expected Result
• Actual Result
• Status (Pass / Fail)
• Severity
• Priority
• Comments

---

## Key Test Areas Covered

### 1. Landing Page Testing

Verified that the landing page loads successfully with all primary UI elements.

Tested components:

* Logo visibility
* Login button
* Sign Up button
* Feature section
* Language tabs
* Embedded video

---

### 2. Navigation & Routing Testing

Validated the behavior of navigation buttons and URL routing.

Examples:

* Sign Up button redirect behavior
* Login button redirect behavior
* Feature button scroll behavior
* Browser back button navigation

Issues discovered:

* Hash based routing (`/#login`, `/#features`) not working correctly
* Direct routes (`/login`, `/features`) work but hash routes do not
* Feature button only changes URL but does not scroll or navigate

---

### 3. Registration Page Testing

Tested user registration workflow including mandatory payment proof upload.

Test scenarios included:

* Sign Up page loading
* Payment receipt image upload
* Form submission validation

Issues discovered:

* Payment receipt is mandatory but **no validation message appears**
* "Create Account" button remains clickable even when receipt is not uploaded
* No user guidance that payment is required before signup

---

### 4. UI and Usability Testing

Several usability issues were observed during testing.

Examples:

* "Start Drafting Free" button displayed even though the application is not free
* QR payment image too small and **not expandable**
* No user feedback when clicking QR image
* Broken navigation behavior for feature links

---

